Eskom said on Tuesday that load-shedding was on the cards for the rest of the week. The power utility announced stage 2 load-shedding from 9am on Tuesday. “There have been delays in returning some generation units to service that were expected to return to service [on Monday],” Eskom said in a statement. “They will now only return during the course of the week. This has put additional pressure on the system and necessitated a continuation of load-shedding.” Eskom said that demand for electricity had increased since January. The power utility provided several tips on how to save electricity: